         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [Recommg ¶ Recommending. ¶  ¶ that ¶  ¶ a holiday be granted to employés in Gardens on 8 hours Anniversary] ¶ His letter wasreturnedto Mon18 April 1871 minuted: 'no objection but no pay for the day...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">71.04.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>James McCulloch</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 4224, vol. 1871 Y, VPRS 1168/P inward correspondence registers, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; item is a register entry only, of a letter dated 11 April 1871.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[Recommg<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Recommending.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a holiday be granted to employés in Gardens on 8 hours Anniversary]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>His letter was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>returned<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>18 April 1871 minuted: 'no objection but no pay for the day'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>fifteenth<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>anniversary of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>adoption<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the eight hours system was celebrated yesterday [Friday, 21<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>April],<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with the customary procession through the city and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">fête</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the Friendly Societies' reserve…The procession started at about 10 minutes to l1 o'clock. At the head was the band of the Carlton Rifles. Then came the committee of the association and the eight hours banner. The different trades, with their several banners, followed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>…<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The procession was a very long one, and must have numbered over 3,000 persons' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 22 April 1871, p. 7)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The building trades had agreed an 8-hour working day on 21 April 1856.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Some trades had negotiated the one-day holiday<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>without loss of pay, but it was not a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>statutory<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>public holiday.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
